<span id="411">And taking comb and mirror, unguents, soap,<br />
I dressed and groomed him as a handmaid might. (411)</span><br />
<span id="412"><em>I</em> boiled the rice, <em>I</em> washed the pots and pans;<br />
And as a mother on her only child,<br />
So did I minister to my good man. (412)</span><br />
<span id="413">For me, who with toil infinite thus worked,<br />
And rendered service with a humble mind,<br />
Rose early, ever diligent and good,<br />
For me he nothing felt save sore dislike. (413)</span><br />
<span id="414">Nay, to his mother and his father he<br />
